Make the statistics of the changes in each release of a project.


Getting Started
===============

Raw output
----------

```
/* Set PATH to point to this directory */
$ cd <your project>
$ relstat.py
```

This command will show the diff stat of each release in latest 6 months.  For
example, the command on linux repo shows below output:
```
               version      files    inserts    deletes       diff
  v5.5-rc2(2019-12-15)          0          0          0          0
  v5.5-rc3(2019-12-23)        571       6529       2991       9520
  v5.5-rc4(2019-12-29)         62        823        570       1393
  v5.5-rc5(2020-01-05)        197       1378        921       2299
  v5.5-rc6(2020-01-13)        244       1577        864       2441
  v5.5-rc7(2020-01-20)        291       2319       2230       4549
      v5.5(2020-01-27)        200       2695       1131       3826
  v5.6-rc1(2020-02-10)      10609     566486     261234     827720
  v5.6-rc2(2020-02-16)        381       8852       5646      14498
  v5.6-rc3(2020-02-24)        412       4400       4132       8532
  v5.6-rc4(2020-03-01)        218       2561       1328       3889
  v5.6-rc5(2020-03-09)        343       3078       1738       4816
  v5.6-rc6(2020-03-15)        297       2561       1068       3629
  v5.6-rc7(2020-03-23)        121        927        436       1363
      v5.6(2020-03-29)        297       3239       1478       4717
  v5.7-rc1(2020-04-12)      10762     541509     277749     819258
  v5.7-rc2(2020-04-19)        332       3258       2150       5408
  v5.7-rc3(2020-04-26)        462       4818       2564       7382
  v5.7-rc4(2020-05-03)        162       1290        605       1895
  v5.7-rc5(2020-05-10)        306       3097       1433       4530
  v5.7-rc6(2020-05-17)        355       2991       1516       4507
